## Run directly

```bash
go test ./...
go run .
```

From another terminal:

```bash
curl http://localhost:8080/
curl http://localhost:8080/healthz
curl http://localhost:8080/readyz
curl http://localhost:8080/metrics
```

Press `Control+C` in the service terminal before starting Docker so port `8080` is free.

## Run as a container

```bash
docker build --tag {{SERVICE_NAME}}:local .
docker run --rm --name {{SERVICE_NAME}} -p 8080:8080 {{SERVICE_NAME}}:local
```

From another terminal:

```bash
curl http://localhost:8080/healthz
docker inspect {{SERVICE_NAME}} --format '{{.Config.User}}'
```

Expected:

```text
ok
nonroot:nonroot
```

